<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-223-868  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 223 868.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Feb 27 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Racal takes 20 percent stake in satellite TV/data service. (RacalElectronics invests in Satellite Information Services)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Racal Electronics PLC (investment activities)Satellite Information Services Corp. (securities).andO;Topic:     InvestmentsSatellite CommunicationsTelevisionService Industry.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>RACAL TAKES 20 PERCENT STAKE IN SATELLITE TV/DATA SERVICE BRACKNELL, ENGLAND,1990 FEB 24 (NB) -- Racal Electronics has taken a 20 percent stake inSatellite Information Services (SIS), the satellite TV and data distributioncompany.andP;  The deal has cost Racal UKP 22 million ($33 million).andM;SIS was awarded a specialized satellite service (SSS) licence for one-to-manydistribution of one-way information over satellite links in October, 1988.andO;Since then, the most public of the company's business has been in supplyingbookmakers with a satellite TV and data feed of races in progress around theworld.andM;SIS's licence is due to be extended by the UK government to allow Europe-widetransmission of its services, permitting the company to operate as abroadcast carrier for all manner of TV and data transmissions, includingbroadcast TV and teletext programmes.andM;Announcing the deal last week, David Elsbury, Racal's chief executive, saidthat the investment gives Racal a share in a first-class business with goodprospects for growth.andM;&quot;It provides an excellent opportunity to work closely with a company whichhas the benefit of a licence enabling it to offer a whole range of newsatellite services.andP;  SIS has extensive experience as well as a significantongoing revenue stream and we look forward to working together to develop newbusiness in this exciting field,&quot; he said.andM;(Steve Gold/19900224/Press Contact: Richard Poston - Racal Group - Tel:0734-782158)</TEXT></DOC>